Manchester City Joins Race for Tottenham’s Modric, Mail Reports

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-06-11T16:30:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-11/manchester-city-joins-race-for-tottenham-s-modric-mail-reports.html
Manchester City  has joined the race
to sign Tottenham midfielder Luka Modric, the Daily Mail said.  City manager  Roberto Mancini  is ready to make a bid of
around 30 million pounds ($49 million) for the 25-year-old
Modric, who has been linked with Manchester United and Chelsea,
the Mail said.  City is ready to triple Modric’s 55,000-pounds-per-week
salary and Chelsea owner Roman Abramovich will match the
Eastlands club in the bidding, the Mail said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  